      <akn:section eId="sec_28:9_204">
        <akn:num>28:9-204</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>After-acquired property; future advances.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:9-204_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Except as otherwise provided in subsection (b), a security agreement may create or provide for a security interest in after-acquired collateral.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:9-204_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A security interest does not attach under a term constituting an after-acquired property clause to:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:9-204_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A security agreement may provide that collateral secures, or that accounts, chattel paper, payment intangibles, or promissory  notes are sold in connection with, future advances or other value, whether or not the advances or value are given pursuant to  commitment.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
